<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,624,2012]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description.—Measurements (m / f). Total length (from apex of head to apex of hemelytra at rest) 16.5– 19.1 / 15.8–18.7; largest width of body 7.4–8.3 / 7.5–8.4; median length of pronotum 3.04–3.44 / 3.12–3.60; greatest pronotal width 5.20–6.24 / 5.44–6.24.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,624,2012]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
General coloration dark brown. Vertex, pronotum, scutellum, part of hemelytra occasionally with hyaline longitudinal stripe (see Smith &amp; Smith 
<emphasis box="[612,670,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">apud</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, R. L." box="[677,818,1626,1652]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="333 - 343" refId="ref60297" refString="Smith, R. L. (1976) Brooding behaviour of a male water bug, Belostoma flumineum (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 49, 333 - 343." type="journal article" year="1976">Smith 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,624,2012]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Body elliptical. Length of anteoculus 0.88–1 length of interoculus; lengths of rostral segments I and II equal; anterior frontogenal suture shorter, equal to, or longer than posterior frontogenal suture; clypeus reaching ocular line; vertex without longitudinal median carina; posterior interocular width 1.47–1.67 times length of anteoculus, and 1.53–1.92 times width of eye; eyes rounded. Pronotum without longitudinal median carina; greatest pronotal width 1.67–1.82 times its length; scutellum not reaching nodal line (
<quantity box="[1150,1326,1826,1852]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="0.28" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.16">0.16–0.40 mm</quantity>
), without longitudinal median carina; prosternal keel prominent, acute at apex (
<figureCitation box="[973,1082,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1685,1709]" captionTargetBox="[433,1176,674,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-337@39.[339,1248,627,1687]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 11. Belostoma candidulum Montandon, 1903, B. horvathi Montandon, 1903, and B. sanctulum Montandon, 1903. B. candidulum. 11A, Prosternal keel (lateral view): specimen from State of São Paulo (SEMC). Scale: 0.50 mm. 11B–D, Phallus: specimen from Chaco, Argentina (MACN 39307). Scale: 1.00 mm. B. horvathi. 11E–F, Prosternal keel (lateral view): 11E, Specimen from State of Minas Gerais (DPIC 1641). 11F, Specimen from State of Minas Gerais (DPIC 1218). 11G–I, Phallus: specimen from State of São Paulo (SEMC 1063). Scale bar: 1.00 mm. B. sanctulum. 11J– K, Prosternal keel (lateral view): 11J, Specimen from State of Espírito Santo (ISNB). 11K, Specimen from State of Rio de Janeiro (DZRJ 17). Scale: 0.50 mm. 11L–N, Phallus: specimen from State of Espírito Santo (ISNB). Scale: 1.00 mm. 11B, 11G and 11L, Dorsal views. 11C, 11H, and 11M, Ventral views. 11D, 11I and 11N, Lateral views. (VED) ventral dilatation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5086456" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5086456/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Pilosity not extending along genital operculum, covering part of connexivum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,624,2012]" lastBlockId="39.[151,1436,152,613]" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[386,523,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1685,1709]" captionTargetBox="[433,1176,674,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-337@39.[339,1248,627,1687]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 11. Belostoma candidulum Montandon, 1903, B. horvathi Montandon, 1903, and B. sanctulum Montandon, 1903. B. candidulum. 11A, Prosternal keel (lateral view): specimen from State of São Paulo (SEMC). Scale: 0.50 mm. 11B–D, Phallus: specimen from Chaco, Argentina (MACN 39307). Scale: 1.00 mm. B. horvathi. 11E–F, Prosternal keel (lateral view): 11E, Specimen from State of Minas Gerais (DPIC 1641). 11F, Specimen from State of Minas Gerais (DPIC 1218). 11G–I, Phallus: specimen from State of São Paulo (SEMC 1063). Scale bar: 1.00 mm. B. sanctulum. 11J– K, Prosternal keel (lateral view): 11J, Specimen from State of Espírito Santo (ISNB). 11K, Specimen from State of Rio de Janeiro (DZRJ 17). Scale: 0.50 mm. 11L–N, Phallus: specimen from State of Espírito Santo (ISNB). Scale: 1.00 mm. 11B, 11G and 11L, Dorsal views. 11C, 11H, and 11M, Ventral views. 11D, 11I and 11N, Lateral views. (VED) ventral dilatation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5086456" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5086456/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 11B–D</figureCitation>
).—Dorsal arms divergent, slightly broader toward apex in dorsal view; ventral diverticulum flattened, relatively broader, more circular, without dorsal caudal protuberance in dorsal and lateral views, and without ventroapical protuberance in lateral and ventral views; caudal lateral margins of ventral diverticulum convex, not sinuous in ventral view; width and length of ventral diverticulum equal in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,152,613]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Comparative notes.—According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L." box="[617,900,272,298]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref59051" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. (1997) Os Heteropteros Aquaticos de Minas Gerais. Guia Introdutorio com Chave de Identificacao para as Especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha, Ed. UFMG, Belo Horizonte, 180 pp." type="book" year="1997">Nieser and Melo (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack, J. A." box="[912,1089,272,298]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref59850" refString="Schnack, J. A. (1973) Clave para determinacion de especies argentinas del genero Belostoma Latreille (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). Revista del Museo de La Plata, 12 (3), 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1973">Schnack (1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack, J. A." box="[1101,1163,272,298]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref59891" refString="Schnack, J. A. (1976) Los Belostomatidae de la Republica Argentina (Hemiptera). In: Ringuelet, R. A. (Ed), Fauna de Agua Dulce de la Republica Argentina, volume 35, Fasciculo 1, Fecic, Buenos Aires, 1 - 66." type="book chapter" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
), and here, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of this group because segments I and II of its rostrum are equal in length. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[370,557,351,377]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="189 - 260" refId="ref56650" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1938) Los Belostomidos americanos. Anales del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales ' Bernardino Rivadavia' Buenos Aires, 39 (155), 189 - 260, 7 pls." type="book chapter" year="1938">De Carlo (1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[570,632,351,377]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref56776" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1956) Especies nuevas de la familia Belostomatidae (Hemiptera) y algunas consideraciones sobre otras poco conocidas. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 19 (3 - 4), 51 - 56." type="journal article" year="1956">1956</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Estevez, A. L." box="[654,834,351,377]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref57207" refString="Estevez, A. L. (1996) Revision Sistematica del Genero Belostoma Latreille (Hemiptera - Heteroptera). Grupos de Belostoma (Belostoma) triangulum, B. (B.) minor, B. (B.) oxyurum, B. (B.) plebejum y B. (B.) denticolle, Doctor thesis, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Museo, Universidad Nacional de La Plata, La Plata, vi + 117 pp, 16 pls." type="book" year="1996">Estévez (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Montandon, A. L." box="[897,1136,351,377]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="359 - 363" refId="ref58941" refString="Montandon, A. L. (1903 b) Especes nouvelles ou peu connues du genre Belostoma appartennant aux collections du Musee National Hongrois. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 1, 359 - 363." type="journal article" year="1903">Montandon (1903b)</bibRefCitation>
, rostral segments I and II are subequal. This discrepancy suggests that this character varies in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[960,1131,390,415]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis box="[960,1131,390,415]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the possibility remains that the discrepancy results from imprecise measuring and is therefore an anomaly (A. L. Melo, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,152,613]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[415,514,509,534]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici">
<emphasis box="[415,514,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. amici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[583,754,509,534]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis box="[583,754,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clear. The 
<typeStatus box="[915,965,508,534]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1105,509,534]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici">
<emphasis box="[1006,1105,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. amici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses all the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[281,451,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis box="[281,451,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The differences between the 
<typeStatus box="[800,862,548,574]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">types</typeStatus>
are small and well within the limits of variability found here in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[314,485,588,613]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis box="[314,485,588,613]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I therefore synonymize 
<taxonomicName box="[779,877,588,613]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amici">
<emphasis box="[779,877,588,613]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. amici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1903" box="[943,1114,588,613]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidulum">
<emphasis box="[943,1114,588,613]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">B. candidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
